The UK&#8217;s Architecture Foundation is launching a free app which explains the architectural significance of over a thousand buildings.The &#8220;London Architecture Guide&#8221; app is packed with information on the city&#8217;s architectural heritage. It can be downloaded from iTunes.The app has an interactive map locating the most significant buildings in the city, and includes a photo and a critical text for each one. It also provides essays on the history of London&#8217;s architecture and event listings of upcoming talks.The app will receive updates and new buildings will be added on a regular basis.-Relaxnews